Reasoning: The paper deals with properties of scalar quantization with a distortion constraint and constrained R\'enyi entropy, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The concept of entropy density and its application to quantization is also relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of source density mismatch on the quantization performance, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS).
